Subject: FR/GB  Oui à la croissance partagée en Afrique, recherche de financement, nos publications, notre charte, formation au Burkina Faso, bonne affaire /// Yes to shared growthin Africa, search for financing, our publications, our charter, training in Burkina
TextBody: Français / English below [https://2tvlo.img.ag.d.sendibm3.com/im/sh/frB_XbBNgFZr.jpg?u=92pJLo34vnrQtTPiT3zso9Y7VRkmj50FLqT] L'accompagnement dans la Croissance Partagée avec l'Afrique pour Prospérer Ensemble... Bonjour, Sommaire de la lettre: 1) Oui à la croissance partagée en Afrique ! 2) Recherche de financement pour VOTRE projet en Afrique 3) Nos publications 4) Notre charte, la garantie Croissance PEACE pour l'Afrique 5) Formation au Burkina Faso 6) Bonne affaire ( chambres froides) Je souhaite devenir un nouvel abonné gratuitement<mailto:contact@croissancepeace.org> La lettre est distribuée à 70 000 lecteurs. Vous pouvez la diffuser aux autorités compétentes. Derniers éditos<https://2tvlo.r.ag.d.sendibm3.com/mk/cl/f/sh/WCPzyXJTZ6uvcwysdYpdV6Sb394ybg6z/UKqFFMJ-hH4q> ***** 1) Oui à la croissance partagée en Afrique ! L'octroi de plans, de programmes et de coopérations, afin de soutenir des actions et activités spécifiques rapidement réalisables, sans garantie aucune des organisations bénéficiaires, ne peut entraîner durablement l’Afrique vers le financement de ses priorités de développement. Il ne suffit pas de construire une école ou d’annuler une dette il convient que la collaboration soit seulement appropriée et efficace. Sans dénigrer certaines collaborations qui peuvent parfois être bénéfiques, force est de constater qu’elles ne sont pas toujours désintéressées. L’Afrique n’a pas besoin d'une aide qui la maintient dans un état de dépendance et, cette façon de procéder risque de la priver de la possibilité de progresser de façon notable et durable en se servant de ses propres ressources, en luttant contre la corruption et en développant ses propres capacités et compétences. Il est désormais souhaitable d’adopter une approche alternative plus réfléchie et participative, en accord avec les populations africaines, pour qu’elles soient en mesure de définir leurs besoins spécifiques et gérer leur avenir par des projets adaptés à leur réalité. Cela permettrait aussi de favoriser le développement des populations locales, renforçant ainsi leur capacité à résoudre les défis auxquels elles doivent faire face. L'Afrique a une volonté tenace de réussir, de se développer et d’innover par elle-même. Ainsi, il ressort du livre intitulé, l'innovation africaine par les femmes : la clé de l’envol du continent vers la prospérité parue en 2023, « que la participation des femmes au sein de la société et dans les activités économiques est en constante augmentation. » Elles deviennent des actrices incontournables du changement, notamment dans le secteur agricole qui, il convient de le rappeler, représente un enjeu central pour l'avenir. La revue Géoéconomie Pour une croissance partagée entre l'Afrique, la Chine et l'Europe, publiée en 2014, révèle qu’ “avec trois fois la taille des États-Unis, l’Afrique sub-saharienne, pourrait même devenir vers 2040 la zone du monde à l’économie la plus dynamique.” L'émergence potentielle de l'Afrique sub-saharienne comme la région du monde détenant l'économie la plus dynamique est une perspective prometteuse et porteuse d'espoir pour l'avenir. Cette région, qui couvre une vaste étendue de territoire aux ressources naturelles riches et variées, regorge d'un potentiel inexploité qui attire de plus en plus l'attention des investisseurs et des acteurs économiques internationaux. C’est pour cette raison qu’il est nécessaire de favoriser son développement de manière durable et efficace et que toutes les parties prenantes s'engagent activement. Les institutions, les entreprises, qu'elles soient françaises ou étrangères, gouvernementales ou non ont un rôle de tout premier plan à jouer dans ce processus en accord avec les autorités locales africaines. En soutenant les africains, les nouveaux acteurs peuvent contribuer à créer un véritable partenariat basé sur l'échange de connaissances et de compétences et permettre la transmission réciproque de savoirs leur permettant de capitaliser sur leur propre savoir-faire, qui est déjà extrêmement riche et varié. Cette synergie entre les connaissances locales et l'expertise étrangère ouvre des perspectives nouvelles et prometteuses pour le développement de l'Afrique. Depuis longtemps la priorité de Croissance PEACE est de favoriser une étroite collaboration et une confiance réciproque égalitaire entre les partenaires européens et africains. Il est désormais temps que les pays africains trouvent leur propre souveraineté et gère par eux-mêmes leur avenir. Cela exige un changement dans les relations commerciales en privilégiant davantage la coopération, en réduisant l'agressivité commerciale et en abandonnant les stratégies unilatérales. Il est désormais temps aussi de respecter les traditions et les coutumes et d'impliquer toutes les parties prenantes pour aboutir finalement à une croissance partagée. L'ONG Croissance PEACE a toujours eu pour ambition de promouvoir cette croissance partagée en s'appuyant sur les complémentarités entre les acteurs impliqués et en mettant l'accent sur une véritable volonté de développement durable et de respect des valeurs humaines. En adoptant ainsi une approche coopérative, les partenaires européens et africains pourront œuvrer ensemble pour relever les défis et saisir les opportunités qui se présenteront. En valorisant les compétences et les ressources de chacun, ils pourront créer des projets durables et équitables, qui profiteront à tous les acteurs impliqués, qu'ils soient économiques, sociaux ou environnementaux. L’avenir de l’Afrique doit se dessiner par les africains ; Croissance PEACE le dit et l’écrit depuis bien longtemps. Voir notre charte.<https://2tvlo.r.ag.d.sendibm3.com/mk/cl/f/sh/WCPzyXJTZ72igzC8zeJJGqcOBvy5rNj7/JPsQ3Fipgd0X> <https://2tvlo.r.ag.d.sendibm3.com/mk/cl/f/sh/WCPzyXJTZ7AVl1PPLjmz2amBKirD75LF/BI6F_q4xi0dR> On est ensemble ! Ludovic Emanuely<mailto:ludovic.emanuely@croissancepeace.org> Président Croissance PEACE 2) Recherche de financement pour votre projet en Afrique En-dehors des perspectives économiques, l’investissement dans les domaines de l’agriculture, l’énergie, la technologie, le numérique, les services, l’éducation et la santé en Afrique, est riche de sens. Les investisseurs de Croissance PEACE en sont de plus en plus conscients. En effet, la crise sanitaire a rebattu les cartes. Partout, dans le monde, les professionnels de l’investissement sont à la recherche de nouvelles opportunités, en revisitant en profondeur leurs stratégies. Ils trouvent leur compte en Afrique, en misant sur la créativité de porteurs de projet ambitieux et visionnaires, le développement de compétences localement, et la participation à une aventure collective. La valeur cardinale et condition première de cette réussite est la confiance mutuelle. Croissance PEACE a créé le cadre de rencontre de ces différents acteurs économiques, et apporte sur le terrain, en Afrique, son expertise aux PME africaines à la recherche d’investisseurs privés à l’international. Si vous êtes en quête de financement pour votre projet d’entreprise, vous pouvez bénéficier de notre soutien en nous envoyant votre Business Plan pour étude. Nous évaluerons le potentiel de rentabilité de votre projet. Si votre projet est retenu, alors, nous mettrons en place un protocole d’accompagnement. Pour rappel, les projets que nous accompagnons doivent avoir un besoin de financement minimum d’EUR 10 millions. Avec mes amitiés, Auguste DAGO Directeur des investissements auguste.dago@croissancepeace.org<mailto:auguste.dago@croissancepeace.org> 3) Nos publications . A Armes égales citoyens ? La stratégie du looser (Intelligence économique) https://www.leseditionsdunet.com/livre/armes-egales-citoyens-la-strategie-du-looser<https://2tvlo.r.ag.d.sendibm3.com/mk/cl/f/sh/WCPzyXJTZ7IIp3cfhpGeoKvyTVkKMmxN/_7N-osWDGDHY> . Le Partenariat Privé-Privé Performé Par le Public (6P) avec l’Afrique ; livre encouragé par l’Union Africaine https://www.leseditionsdunet.com/livre/partenariat-prive-prive-performe-par-le-public-le-6p<https://2tvlo.r.ag.d.sendibm3.com/mk/cl/f/sh/WCPzyXJTZ7Q5t5pw3ukKa55lcIdRcUZV/5t_GmmJu-PlS> . L’innovation africaine par les femmes ; seul livre consacré exclusivement sur le sujet https://www.leseditionsdunet.com/livre/linnovation-africaine-par-les-femmes<https://2tvlo.r.ag.d.sendibm3.com/mk/cl/f/sh/WCPzyXJTZ7Xsx83CQ0E0LpFYl5WYsCBd/ogFyDSTfeCAZ> 4) Notre charte, la garantie Croissance PEACE pour l'Afrique La mission que s’est donnée l’ONG Croissance PEACE dès sa fondation est de participer activement aux cotés des africains à la croissance et au développement souverain de l’Afrique, aux plans économique et sociétal. Dans l’équité et le respect des cultures locales africaines, nous sommes animés par la ferme volonté d’apporter une contribution significative au processus de développement de l’Afrique. Pour nous, cela passe par le progrès technique à travers l’industrialisation de l’Afrique, la transformation locale des matières premières, le développement des pôles d’innovations, le transfert de technologie, l’accession par l’Afrique à ses propres innovations maitrisées, l’amélioration continue des services dans les secteurs publics et privés. Ainsi, Croissance PEACE entend aider à promouvoir la politique africaine, sous quelque forme que ce soit (médias, forums, associations, labels) dans le monde. Elle interviendra de façon indéfectible dans la lutte contre « les prédateurs » du continent et toute action qui va à l’encontre des intérêts des populations et des cultures africaines. ​ Les sept principes fondamentaux qui guident Croissance PEACE pour l’Afrique: 1. Être un Facilitateur pour accompagner les négociations difficiles 2. Poursuivre inlassablement la recherche de l’intérêt général 3. Élaborer des stratégies adaptées pour une industrialisation africaine, point de départ de tout développement véritable 4. Sélectionner pour les entrepreneurs sur l’Afrique, à leur demande, les partenaires les plus compétents à travers le monde, pour leurs activités économiques 5. Accompagner les États et entreprises africaines dans leurs efforts de mobilisation de financement pour les projets structurants 6. Travailler avec les dirigeants africains dans la voie d’une Afrique autodéterminée, responsable, souveraine, fière et respectée qui gère son avenir 7. Créer des labels de qualité, spécifiquement africains, des produits distribués en Afrique, garantissant ainsi leur qualité (industries agroalimentaires, cosmétiques, fabricants locaux, importateurs) En découle ces 7 points prioritaires pour l’Afrique de notre charte : . Priorisation à l’emploi local, facilitation pour un management local . Transfert de technologies en croissance partagée vers l’Afrique . Développement économique, sociale et environnemental d’une industrie de la transformation . Favoriser l’équilibre sur les contrats signés avec les entités étrangères au pays . Respect des valeurs sociales, sociétales et culturelles locales . Respect du principe de la non-ingérence . Donner une image juste de l’Afrique, porteuse de solutions pour le monde 5) Formation au Burkina Faso J’ai effectué une mission du 18 au 28 juillet dans le cadre d’un appui au renforcement de la justice militaire et de la justice de proximité (AJUMJUP) au Burkina Faso. Le Burkina Faso est un pays qui a fait l’objet de deux coups d’État militaire, le premier le 23 janvier 2022 puis le second huit mois plus tard le 30 septembre 2022 coup d’État à la tête duquel le capitaine Ibrahim TRAORÉ s’est autoproclamé le nouveau chef du pays. Ces deux coups d’État sont liés principalement à l’incapacité des autorités à faire face aux attaques de groupes criminels djihadistes qui sévissent surtout dans le nord et l’est du pays depuis 2015. A l’issue de ce deuxième coup d’État le retrait des soldats français engagés depuis 13 ans dans la lutte anti-djihadiste au Sahel a été demandé par le gouvernement ainsi que le départ de l’ambassadeur de France qui n’a pas été remplacé depuis. Dans ce contexte de conflit armé et devant le risque croissant de graves violations du droit international humanitaire et des droits de l’homme, l’Assemblée Législative de Transition du Burkina Faso (ALT) a décidé de modifier le code de justice militaire le 16 février 2023 et de créer une prévôté auprès des unités déployées dans les opérations intérieures. La prévôté exerce la justice au sein des armées et garantit la discipline des troupes tout en protégeant la population des exactions dans les zones de guerre. Il fallait former ces militaires burkinabès pour qu’ils puissent travailler dans le cadre de la lutte contre le terrorisme. La Commission européenne a financé le projet à hauteur d’environ quatre milliards de francs CFA et confié à l’Ong suisse Coginta sa mise en œuvre qui comportait aussi la construction de cellules. J’ai été recrutée, en tant que française, experte internationale, spécialiste en justice militaire ayant travaillé quatorze années dans l’armée possédant une bonne connaissance de l’Afrique pour former les prévôts burkinabès. Je me suis déplacée 10 jours à Ouagadougou et ai formé ainsi trente stagiaires m’appuyant sur une législation qui est destinée à être refondée selon le président de la transition Ibrahim TRAORE « pour doter le pays d’une Constitution qui soit le reflet des aspirations de nos populations ». Les burkinabès considèrent que le canevas occidental n’est plus le mieux adapté et qu’il convient d’innover à partir de l’existant. Cette nouvelle expérience avec des personnes motivées m’a fait reprendre contact avec la culture africaine, le langage africain et la bonne humeur et j’ai voulu terminer cette formation par une note plus légère en parlant de médiation car les pays africains ont dans leur culture une longue tradition de règlement pacifique des conflits considérant, à juste titre, que « si des personnes ne se comprennent pas c’est qu’elles ne se parlent pas ». Janine Stern Avocate générale honoraire Médiateure assermentée à la cour d’appel de Paris, Experte internationale janine.stern@croissancepeace.org<mailto:janine.stern@croissancepeace.org> Autres formations Croissance PEACE<https://2tvlo.r.ag.d.sendibm3.com/mk/cl/f/sh/WCPzyXJTZ7fg1AGSm5hg7ZPLtsPg7tnl/ebCulRHdgCMl> 6) Bonne affaire.... . 4 chambres froides en état de marche et ayant peu servi Livraison gratuite FOB. 3 contenairs 40 pieds qui resteront vôtre. . un salle de conservation négative (20m x 15m x 3,20m ) . une salle positive de préparation (19,80m x 14,80m x 3,30m) . deux salles positives de stockage (19,80m x 7,80m x 3,30m). Faire proposition:contact@croissancepeace.org<mailto:contact@croissancepeace.org> Pensons positif et agissons constructif ! Bien cordialement [https://2tvlo.img.ag.d.sendibm3.com/im/sh/ctDQcvtz3oyG.png?u=92pJLo34vnrQtbCmVHGEtdDtFbXvVy7V3Sb] Ludovic EMANUELY President – Croissance PEACE Chede- RC gend- IIIC +33 6 80 26 97 19 (Direct et Whatsapp) www.croissancepeace.org<https://2tvlo.r.ag.d.sendibm3.com/mk/cl/f/sh/WCPzyXJTZ7nT5CTj8BBLtJZ92fInNbPt/U4fqWp4lOJEI> ludovic.emanuely@croissancepeace.org<mailto:ludovic.emanuely@croissancepeace.org> English [https://2tvlo.img.ag.d.sendibm3.com/im/sh/frB_XbBNgFZr.jpg?u=92pJLo34vnrQtTPiT3zso9Y7VRkmj50FLqT]<https://2tvlo.r.ag.d.sendibm3.com/mk/cl/f/sh/WCPzyXJTZ7vG9EgzUGf1f3iwBSBudJ21/3ePIbQZ4nCt1> Shared Growth With Africa to prosper Together .. Hello, Letter summary: 1) Yes to shared growth in Africa! 2) Search for financing for YOUR project in Africa 3) Our publications 4) Our charter, the PEACE Growth guarantee for Africa 5) Training in Burkina Faso 6) Good deal (cold rooms) I want to become a new subscriber for free<mailto:contact@croissancepeace.org> The letter is distributed to 70,000 readers. You can distribute it to the competent authorities. Latest editorials<https://2tvlo.r.ag.d.sendibm3.com/mk/cl/f/sh/WCPzyXJTZ833DGuFqM8hQnsjKF51t0e9/-_6odvzSftzL> ***** 1) Yes to shared growth in Africa! The granting of plans, programs and cooperation, in order to support specific actions and activities that can be quickly implemented, without guarantee from any of the beneficiary organizations, cannot sustainably lead Africa towards financing its development priorities. It is not enough to build a school or cancel a debt; the collaboration must only be appropriate and effective. Without denigrating certain collaborations which can sometimes be beneficial, it is clear that they are not always disinterested. Africa does not need aid which keeps it in a state of dependence and this way of proceeding risks depriving it of the possibility of making significant and lasting progress by using its own resources, by fighting against corruption and by developing their own capacities and skills. It is now desirable to adopt a more thoughtful and participatory alternative approach, in agreement with the African populations, so that they are able to define their specific needs and manage their future through projects adapted to their reality. This would also promote the development of local populations, thus strengthening their capacity to resolve the challenges they face. Africa has a tenacious desire to succeed, develop and innovate on its own. Thus, it emerges from the book entitled, African innovation by women: the key to the continent's flight towards prosperity published in 2023, "that the participation of women within society and in economic activities is constantly increase. » They are becoming essential actors of change, particularly in the agricultural sector which, it should be remembered, represents a central issue for the future. The journal Geoeconomics For shared growth between Africa, China and Europe, published in 2014, reveals that “with three times the size of the United States, sub-Saharan Africa could even become around 2040 the area of the world with the most dynamic economy.” The potential emergence of sub-Saharan Africa as the region with the most dynamic economy in the world is a promising and hopeful prospect for the future. This region, which covers a vast expanse of territory with rich and varied natural resources, is full of untapped potential which is increasingly attracting the attention of investors and international economic players. This is why it is necessary to promote its development in a sustainable and efficient manner and for all stakeholders to actively engage. Institutions and companies, whether French or foreign, governmental or not, have a leading role to play in this process in agreement with local African authorities. By supporting Africans, new players can help create a real partnership based on the exchange of knowledge and skills and allow the reciprocal transmission of knowledge allowing them to capitalize on their own know-how, which is already extremely rich and varied. . This synergy between local knowledge and foreign expertise opens up new and promising perspectives for the development of Africa. Croissance PEACE's priority has long been to promote close collaboration and equal mutual trust between European and African partners. It is now time for African countries to find their own sovereignty and manage their future on their own. This requires a change in trade relations by emphasizing more cooperation, reducing trade aggressiveness and abandoning unilateral strategies. Now is also the time to respect traditions and customs and involve all stakeholders to ultimately achieve shared growth. The NGO Croissance PEACE has always aimed to promote this shared growth by relying on the complementarities between the actors involved and by emphasizing a real desire for sustainable development and respect for human values. By adopting a cooperative approach, European and African partners will be able to work together to meet the challenges and seize the opportunities that arise. By promoting everyone's skills and resources, they will be able to create sustainable and equitable projects, which will benefit all stakeholders involved, whether economic, social or environmental. The future of Africa must be shaped by Africans; Croissance PEACE has been saying and writing this for a long time. See our charter.<https://2tvlo.r.ag.d.sendibm3.com/mk/cl/f/sh/28xHLtxYQ4yaod9wlzs0mUDpSpsC1B7p4L/ziWy1dp1rWP3> We are together ! Ludovic Emanuely<mailto:ludovic.emanuely@croissancepeace.org> President Croissance Peace 2) Search for financing for your project in Africa Apart from economic prospects, investment in the fields of agriculture, energy, technology, digital, services, education and health in Africa is rich in meaning. Croissance PEACE investors are increasingly aware of this. Indeed, the health crisis has reshuffled the cards. All over the world, investment professionals are looking for new opportunities, thoroughly revisiting their strategies. They find their benefit in Africa, by banking on the creativity of ambitious and visionary project leaders, the development of skills locally, and participation in a collective adventure. The cardinal value and primary condition for this success is mutual trust. Croissance PEACE has created the framework for meeting these different economic actors, and brings its expertise on the ground, in Africa, to African SMEs looking for private investors internationally. If you are looking for financing for your business project, you can benefit from our support by sending us your Business Plan for study. We will assess the profitability potential of your project. If your project is selected, then we will put in place a support protocol. As a reminder, the projects we support must have a minimum financing requirement of EUR 10 million. My friendships, Auguste DAGO Director of Investments auguste.dago@croissancepeace.org<mailto:auguste.dago@croissancepeace.org> 3) Our publications . A Equal arms citizens? The loser's strategy (Business intelligence) https://www.leseditionsdunet.com/livre/armes-egales-citoyens-la-strategie-du-looser<https://2tvlo.r.ag.d.sendibm3.com/mk/cl/f/sh/28xHLtxYQ4z6zDp5XX4dIxMPtkA3b7xuVN/834vUDXHrheu> . The Private-Private Partnership Performed and Pushed by the Public (6P) with Africa; book encouraged by the African Union https://www.leseditionsdunet.com/livre/partenariat-prive-prive-performe-par-le-public-le-6p<https://2tvlo.r.ag.d.sendibm3.com/mk/cl/f/sh/28xHLtxYQ4zd9oUEJ4HFpQV0KeRvB4nzwP/viwx6ak8HmsF> . African innovation by women; only book devoted exclusively to the subject https://www.leseditionsdunet.com/livre/linnovation-africaine-par-les-femmes<https://2tvlo.r.ag.d.sendibm3.com/mk/cl/f/sh/28xHLtxYQ509KP9N4bTsLtdalYjml1e5NR/5nOn8MI4IkfG> 4) Our charter, the Croissance PEACE guarantee for Africa The mission that the NGO Croissance PEACE has given itself since its foundation is to actively participate alongside Africans in the growth and sovereign development of Africa, on an economic and societal level. In fairness and respect for local African cultures, we are driven by the firm desire to make a significant contribution to the development process in Africa. For us, this involves technical progress through the industrialization of Africa, the local processing of raw materials, the development of innovation centers, the transfer of technology, the accession by Africa to its own innovations mastered, the continuous improvement of services in the public and private sectors. Thus, Croissance PEACE intends to help promote African policy, in whatever form (media, forums, associations, labels) around the world. It will intervene unwaveringly in the fight against “the predators” of the continent and any action that goes against the interests of African populations and cultures. ​ The seven fundamental principles that guide PEACE Growth for Africa: 1. Be a Facilitator to support difficult negotiations 2. Tirelessly pursue the search for the general interest 3. Develop appropriate strategies for African industrialization, the starting point for all true development 4. Select for entrepreneurs in Africa, at their request, the most competent partners throughout the world, for their economic activities 5. Support African States and companies in their efforts to mobilize financing for structuring projects 6. Work with African leaders towards a self-determined, responsible, sovereign, proud and respected Africa that manages its future 7. Create quality labels, specifically African, for products distributed in Africa, thus guaranteeing their quality (food industries, cosmetics, local manufacturers, importers) This results in these 7 priority points for Africa from our charter: . Prioritization of local employment, facilitation for local management . Shared growth technology transfer to Africa . Economic, social and environmental development of a processing industry . Promote balance in contracts signed with foreign entities in the country . Respect for local social, societal and cultural values . Respect for the principle of non-interference . Give a fair image of Africa, a provider of solutions for the world 5) Training in Burkina Faso I carried out a mission from July 18 to 28 as part of support for the strengthening of military justice and local justice (AJUMJUP) in Burkina Faso. Burkina Faso is a country which was the subject of two military coups, the first on January 23, 2022 then the second eight months later on September 30, 2022, led by Captain Ibrahim TRAORÉ. He is self-proclaimed the new leader of the country. These two coups are mainly linked to the inability of the authorities to deal with attacks by jihadist criminal groups which have been raging mainly in the north and east of the country since 2015. At the end of this second coup d'état, the withdrawal of French soldiers engaged for 13 years in the anti-jihadist fight in the Sahel was requested by the government as well as the departure of the French ambassador who was not since replaced. In this context of armed conflict and faced with the growing risk of serious violations of international humanitarian and human rights law, the Transitional Legislative Assembly of Burkina Faso (ALT) decided to modify the code of military justice on February 16 2023 and to create a provost marshal for units deployed in domestic operations. The provost exercises justice within the armies and guarantees the discipline of the troops while protecting the population from abuses in war zones. It was necessary to train these Burkinabè soldiers so that they could work in the fight against terrorism. The European Commission financed the project to the tune of around four billion CFA francs and entrusted the Swiss NGO Coginta with its implementation, which also included the construction of cells. I was recruited, as a Frenchwoman, an international expert, a specialist in military justice having worked fourteen years in the army with a good knowledge of Africa to train the Burkinabè provosts. I traveled to Ouagadougou for 10 days and trained thirty trainees based on legislation which is intended to be overhauled according to the president of the transition Ibrahim TRAORE "to provide the country with a Constitution which reflects the aspirations of our people.” The Burkinabè consider that the Western framework is no longer the best suited and that it is appropriate to innovate based on what already exists. This new experience with motivated people made me reconnect with African culture, African language and good humor and I wanted to end this training on a lighter note by talking about mediation because African countries have in their culture a long tradition of peaceful conflict resolution considering, rightly, that “if people don't understand each other, it's because they don't talk to each other”. Janine Stern Honorary General Counsel Sworn mediator at the Paris Court of Appeal, International expert janine.stern@croissancepeace.org<mailto:janine.stern@croissancepeace.org> <https://2tvlo.r.ag.d.sendibm3.com/mk/cl/f/sh/28xHLtxYQ50fUzoVq8gUsMmBCT1eKyUAoT/O3TmmYF7Qf6n> Other Croissance PEACE training courses<https://2tvlo.r.ag.d.sendibm3.com/mk/cl/f/sh/28xHLtxYQ51BfaTebft7OpuldNJVuvKGFV/_fzAnx1Db5zp> 6) Good deals.... . 4 cold rooms in working order and having little use Free FOB shipping. 3 40 foot containers which will remain yours. . a negative conservation room (20m x 15m x 3.20m) . a positive preparation room (19.80m x 14.80m x 3.30m) . two positive storage rooms (19.80m x 7.80m x 3.30m). Make a proposal: contact@croissancepeace.org<mailto:contact@croissancepeace.org> Think positive and act constructively!

Subject: Reduce your business costs with real-time monitoring
TextBody: To AGRISTO nv, Belgium, Hi there, I'm Vasil Ivanov from XSoft Ltd, a software company. We make custom ERP systems and connect them to your production lines for real-time monitoring. Usually, due to the high costs of personalization, regular ERP systems are not directly connected to production, and manual recording is required. This leads to numerous errors that increase production costs! Therefore, we have implemented our own XERP+XMOM solution for real-time planning and monitoring, which quickly integrates into any production process and optimizes the cost of the final product. Why Real-Time Production Monitoring is crucial: * Helps in better planning of raw materials in the warehouse and saving working capital * Reduces costs by optimizing various production activities * Allows you to simulate production campaigns and plan labor and materials * You can predict with high accuracy the need for new capacities, raw materials or workers * Monitors the quality of the finished product according to a number of parameters * Prevents machine problems and reduces accidents Why Choose Us? We have experience in various industries, which means we work fast and save you money. Our software is user-friendly, and we offer ongoing support. We've worked with companies like Stomana Industry, Zagorka (owned by Heineken), TPP Maritsa Iztok 2, BELLA Bulgaria, Trapezitsa, Bimko, Econt, Nestl?, W?rth, Monbat, EL BAT, Interlogistika, Magma Pak, Vlanel, Plexistab Bulgaria, Stabil Agro Trade, Dormakaba Bulgaria, Green To Go, Dunapak-Rodina, etc. Even if you have an ERP system without MOM monitoring, we can help. We've integrated successfully with Microsoft and SAP. If you're thinking about automating your production, would you be open to an online meeting to discuss your options? I look forward to discussing how we can help your business. Please let me know a convenient time for our online meeting.

Subject: Voitura Group
TextBody: Dears, I hope this email finds you well. I’m thrilled to introduce you to Voitura Group, a trusted and dependable partner in the realm of transportation and forwarding services. Our expertise spans across a wide spectrum of industries, catering to automotive, food and beverage, industrial and manufacturing, retail, e-commerce, electronics, high technology, FMCG, and ADR Goods sectors. Discover Voitura Group: At Voitura Group – https://voitura.eu/about/ we are dedicated to revolutionizing logistics solutions for businesses across multiple sectors. Our strong presence in Europe and commitment to innovation set us apart. Global Reach: Seamless transportation and forwarding solutions across Western, Eastern, and Central Europe, as well as the Nordic region. Our Specialties: * Automotive Sector: We offer efficient transportation solutions for automotive manufacturers, suppliers, and dealerships. Our services ensure timely delivery of vehicles, parts, and components, supporting the automotive industry's intricate supply chain. * Food and Beverage Sector: Our transportation services specialize in the safe and timely delivery of perishable and non-perishable food products. From farm to table, we ensure that food and beverages reach their destinations in optimal condition. * Industrial and Manufacturing Sector: With our robust logistics network, we facilitate the seamless movement of industrial goods and equipment. Our expertise in handling heavy machinery and sensitive materials ensures reliable transportation for the manufacturing industry. * Retail and E-commerce: We provide end-to-end transportation solutions for retailers and e-commerce businesses. From distribution centers to customer doorsteps, our services ensure swift and accurate deliveries, enhancing customer satisfaction. * Electronics and High Technology: Our specialized transportation services cater to delicate electronics and high-tech equipment. We ensure the safe handling and transportation of sensitive devices, supporting the innovation-driven technology sector. * Fast-Moving Consumer Goods (FMCG): We offer rapid and efficient transportation solutions for FMCG companies. Our services help these businesses maintain a steady supply of products on store shelves, meeting consumer demand effectively. * Apparel, Durables, and Retail Goods (ADR Goods): Our transportation services cover the diverse needs of the apparel, durables, and retail goods industries. From fashion items to household durables, we provide reliable transportation to keep businesses moving. By tailoring our transportation services to the unique requirements of each sector, we ensure that businesses can focus on their core operations while we handle the complexities of logistics and distribution. Our commitment to efficiency, reliability, and customer satisfaction sets us apart as a trusted partner for transportation needs across these diverse industries. Thank you for considering Voitura Group as your trusted partner for comprehensive transportation and forwarding solutions. We look forward to the opportunity of collaborating with you. [signature_1483807214] Deividas Kalinauskas Head of Business Development Mobile: +370 630 96 621

Subject: Count down
TextBody: Bekijk dit bericht in je browser<https://cdn.flxml.eu/r-198b9480846b609c235bffb924773c887af63cb0de33cb3b> [https://cdn.flxml.eu/dyn/tpl_attributes/user_images/user_1219_images/piet_kerst_banner.jpg?v=1694776908316] Count Down Nog 100 dagen tot Kerstmis! 🎅 Tijd om aan de voorbereidingen te denken. 🤔 Hier al een sneak peek van Piet en Hilde, al helemaal in de kerstsfeer, ter voorbereiding op de lancering van de nieuwe 'Piet by BergHOFF' RECYCLED collectie. Kerstmis draait om het geven van liefde en genegenheid, en wat is een betere manier om medewerkers, relaties of dierbaren te verrassen dan met een onvergetelijk cadeau? Kookgerei wordt dagelijks gebruikt en met een BergHOFF-geschenk ben je zeker van een blijvende herinnering. Voor elke prijsklasse hebben we iets unieks! En het beste van alles is dat we het cadeau persoonlijk voor je kunnen maken met gravures, sleeves, of zelfs een unieke boodschap. Laten we samen iets speciaals creëren! 🎁🎁 Onderstaande knop naar de standaard prijslijsten, volumeprijzen op aanvrag en een overzicht van de "end-of-life" aan interessante prijzen. Wil je de files graag in excell? Stuur maar een mailtje Laten we samen van deze kerst een onvergetelijk feest maken en neem contact op! 🌟 Tel +32 (11) 922222

Subject: Meet Western Michigan at Anuga
TextBody: Dear Mr. Wallays, I'm contacting you as I estimate that you will be present at this year’s Anuga - either with an own stand or as a visitor. Therefore I would like to introduce the organization The Right Place as well as me – the official representative of The Right Place Inc. in Europe – and offer you a meeting at the upcoming Anuga. The Right Place, Inc. is a regional non-profit economic development organization in West Michigan – located directly between Chicago and Detroit, with Grand Rapids as the state’s second-largest city. Our free-of-charge services – for companies who have future plans expanding into or inside the USA – include for example: * Location Services - Site selection, Incentive and financial (tax) assistance discovery and access, etc. * Business Services – Law regulations and certifications, HR recruiting services, Customs support services. * Manufacturing Assistance Services - Workforce training and certification, Business-to-business learning programs, Conferences, etc. * Innovation Assistance Services - Commercialization process discovery and referral assistance, University and technology transfer access and collaboration support, Intellectual Property discovery, benchmarking and marketing support, Local, state, and federal government access, etc. In our dynamic, growing industry community, you will find: * West Michigan is home to over 300 food and beverage manufacturing establishments, over 200 are located directly in the Grand Rapids Region. * 2nd most agriculturally diverse state in the nation with over 300+ products - right behind California. * Global companies like Nestlé, ConAgra Foods, and the Kellogg Company have chosen West Michigan as a location for significant operations. * Michigan is surrounded almost 18.000 km of freshwater shoreline and borders four of the five Great Lakes. West Michigan hosts several large scale wastewater treatment facilities with excess capacity throughout the region. All this proves that West Michigan is a region which might be a good fit for you to increase their US-activities. With great interest I’m looking forward to your reply and if a meeting at the Anuga would be interesting for you, I’d be pleased to meet you there. Please let me know your preferred time and your stand number. Markus Wellmann The Right Place, Inc. [Western.png [6159 Bytes]] Email: markus.wellmann@pm-p.de<mailto:Markus.Wellmann@pm-p.de> Cell: +49 163 / 6111972 Lyoner Str. 34 | 60528 Frankfurt | Germany Phone: +49 69 668 077 0 DISCLAIMER: This message may contain confidential and/or privileged information. If you are not the addressee or authorized to receive this for the addressee, you must not use, copy, disclose or take any action based on this message or any information herein. If you have received this message in error, please advise the sender immediately by reply e-mail and delete this message. Thank you for your cooperation. All company and personal data will be treated in full confidentiality.

Subject: Export friet naar iraq
TextBody: Goedendag, Ik stuur een bericht voor mijn cliënt hij heeft jaren ervaring met de handel in voedselwaren waaronder friet binnen Irak, maar hij heeft de friet vanuit Azië in laten kopen en nu zoekt hij een gemiddelde kwaliteit friet, met de formaat 9*9mm. 2. De verpakking graag in 1kgx12 zakken. 3.we zouden zo snel mogelijk willen opstarten, graag willen we een paar examples uitproberen. De vraag is wanneer jullie zouden kunnen leveren. 4. Graag willen we dat jullie de transport faciliteren tot umm qasr Basrah, iraq 5. We beginnen met 1 container van 26 ton en bouwen dat steeds meer op totdat de friet vanuit Azië helemaal stopt, nu verhandelt mijn cliënt 10 containers per maand en het groeit. 6. Mn cliënt vind het ook belangrijk dat hij de enige in het land levert 7. Wat zullen de prijzen inclusief en exclusief transport zijn, per ton. Graag hoor ik snel een antwoord terug, Asthar Corp.

Subject: Pulizia e servizi Stand Fieristici
TextBody: Sei alla ricerca di un'impresa di pulizie efficiente e disponibile con orari elastici? [https://9jsxq.img.ag.d.sendibm3.com/im/sh/nRHw8lup8nUZ.png?u=WtVElij8PJZGcPbLG080XlY6VU69akaL] Questo è il tuo titolo. [https://9jsxq.img.ag.d.sendibm3.com/im/sh/ociV16g8aFyP.jpeg?u=WtVElij8PJZGcrw3SQWMdgiMZJTyZUIP] Il tuo titolo qui Salve, siamo l'impresa di pulizie Fiera Michele, con esperienza trentennale e personale qualificato garantiamo un servizio di pulizia ottimale. Il nostro scopo principale è creare ambienti puliti, ordinati ed armoniosi nella quale il cliente possa sentirsi a suo completo agio. Subject: export to Georgia
TextBody: Hello Kateryna, Is your request still valid? If not, I will close down this case. Do not hesitate if you have further questions. Kr, Marieke --------------- Original Message --------------- From: Marieke Van Landschoot [marieke.vanlandschoot@agristo.com] Sent: 12/09/2023 06:33 To: easterneu@elcoactive.com Subject: RE: export to Georgia [ thread::ZkaEikB0Hh69U2AdHZiJgXQ:: ] Dear Kateryna, Please find below our requirements in order to set up a private label: MOQ of 500 ton per SKU per year We ask a financial guarantee of € 2000 per SKU to start up. After the MOQ is exceeded we transfer this amount back. Agristo will arrange everything to produce the foil with our partners. Designs come from the customer If the design is ready, it takes up to 2 months for the foil to be ready to go into production Afterwards if expected volumes are clear we could make sure to have a minimum volume on stock so it would take 1 week then from order to delivery. Attached you will also find a pricelist, giving a view on our reference price. Additional questions from our side: Do you already purchase frozen (potato) products? What is your experience in this field? What volumes of fries per SKU do you do annually? What is your market strategy? Who are your customers?

Subject: Vendor Registration
TextBody: Dear Sir/Madam We require applications from vendors and suppliers to offer us the essential services in our new and ongoing projects in the United Arab Emirates. This is to notify you that we have reviewed your company's profile, your knowledge and experience will be beneficial to the ongoing projects of Power Petroleum Industry (PPI) this 2023/2024 session in United Arab Emirates Operation Centre. We welcome interest and application of all eligible vendors and suppliers from all over the world to participate in these projects; if you are willing, please express your interest by requesting an EOI and Sellers Questionnaire. We are happy and eager to begin a fruitful business relationship with your esteemed company.

Subject: Stay Informed, Stay Ahead: With Freyr Regulatory Newsletters
TextBody: Dear Sir/Madam, Warm greetings! Do you find it challenging to constantly monitor global Regulatory changes? Do you struggle to keep up-to-date with the ever-evolving Regulatory developments, policies, compliance requirements, and industry news? If yes, we have an ideal solution for you: subscribe to Freyr's Regulatory Intelligence Newsletters. Our periodic newsletters grant you seamless access to the latest global Regulatory developments, delivered straight to your inbox. Here are some noteworthy features of our Regulatory newsletters: * Extensive Coverage: A comprehensive range of Regulatory information tailored to your needs. We ensure you have access to a broad spectrum of industry-specific Regulatory intelligence. * Timely Updates: Up-to-date information on new laws, regulations, guidelines, and Regulatory actions, while you get the flexibility to choose how frequently you receive these updates. * Customization & Personalization: Tailored information with customization options for the newsletters – specific segments, markets, topics, and product types based on the organizational requirement. * User-friendly: Our newsletters feature easy-to-read content, with concise summaries of Regulatory changes and links to relevant sources for further reference. Our Regulatory intelligence newsletters can serve as an invaluable resource for staying informed, adapting your compliance strategies, and effectively navigating the ever-changing Regulatory landscape. In this regard, we would like to present Freyr's Regulatory Intelligence capabilities to you in detail. Please let us know a good time to connect to discuss this further. Thank you, and I am looking forward to hearing from you.

Subject: Richiesta riscontro su V/s interesse ad una proposta su Ghiaccio Sintetico Glaice
TextBody: Gent.mo/a buongiorno, nei mesi scorsi Le ho inviato una breve presentazione dell'Azienda Glaice Srls. Azienda di recente costituzione che si occupa della produzione e la commercializzazione di articoli utili per l’imballo e la spedizione di prodotti deperibili, di qualsiasi natura, che necessitano del mantenimento della catena del freddo. Con la presente gradirei sapere se l'avete ricevuta e se siete interessati ad una nostra proposta? Per maggiori informazioni può visitare il sito www.glaice.it<http://www.glaice.it> Se invece preferisce non ricevere ulteriori nostre comunicazioni ce lo comunichi, scusandoci per il disturbo, cancelleremo il suo indirizzo email dal nostro archivio. In attesa di un Suo riscontro, porgo Cordiali Saluti Francesco Mercante Resp.Commerciale Glaice Srls P.iva: 01888620893 Sede Operativa: C/da Bafù, n.10 96015 Francofonte (SR) Tel.095-2882746 Ai sensi dell'art. 13 GDPR 679/16, informiamo che i nostri archivi comprendono indirizzi di posta elettronica relativi a persone fisiche, aziende, enti con i quali sono intercorse precedenti comunicazioni, contatti commerciali e provengono da elenchi di pubblico dominio reperibili su internet, presso le Camere di Commercio o che hanno spontaneamente fornito il loro indirizzo di posta elettronica in occasione di contatti diretti. Informiamo inoltre che tutte le caselle di posta sono caselle aziendali e, in quanto tali, vengono utilizzate per comunicazioni in ambito lavorativo. Pertanto, per esigenze connesse con l'attività operativa, qualsiasi messaggio, sia in uscita che in entrata, potrebbe essere letto da soggetti diversi dal mittente e/o destinatario. Nel caso in cui gli interessati desiderassero che il loro indirizzo di posta elettronica venisse rimosso dal nostro archivio, ovvero per l'esercizio dei diritti di cui agli artt. 15-22 possono scrivere al titolare del trattamento. Le informazioni contenute in questa comunicazione e gli eventuali documenti allegati hanno carattere confidenziale e sono a uso esclusivo del destinatario. Nel caso questa comunicazione Vi sia pervenuta per errore, VI preghiamo di darci prontamente avviso e di cancellare quanto ricevuto.

Subject: Meeting Request_Anuga Oct 9-10th, 2023
TextBody: Dear team AGRISTO nv, Your company caught our attention due to its strong portfolio and international potential. Therefore, we would like to have a conversation with you and meet you during ANUGA 2023. At Invest Alberta<https://investalberta.ca/>, we provide free support to companies looking to invest or further expand in Alberta, Canada. Alberta is an interesting business location in the food industry. Some of Alberta's key strengths are: * Alberta is one of the world's leading producers of commodities such as grains, pulses and livestock. Alberta offers companies the opportunity to produce high quality processed agricultural products and add value. * At 8%, Alberta has the lowest corporate tax rate in Canada and the seventh lowest compared to U.S. states. * The province's food and beverage industry is the largest manufacturing sector in Western Canada. The plant protein market is worth $14.8 billion. * The province of Alberta offers companies strategic access to the U.S. market because of its geographic location, and with an excellent transportation system, Alberta helps companies deliver and distribute their products efficiently. Given these factors, the senior representative from Invest Alberta, Nicola Michels, would love to meet with you during ANUGA on October 9 or 10. We can discuss how we can assist you with your potential market entry or expansion in Canada, free of charge. I look forward to hearing from you and meeting you in person at ANUGA.

Subject: Access a new customer base in 2024
TextBody: Find out why you should exhibit [https://event.montgomerygroup.com/t/1nmVoPwfuGoKys.png]<https://event.montgomerygroup.com/c/11x25g9tnDO6ONsRysHdzw84> View this email online<https://event.montgomerygroup.com/q/13W7Q1jyn93wU3m75JmIz/wv> [https://event.montgomerygroup.com/i/amf_angus_montgomery/project_11/PG24/Email_headers/PPG24_ExProm_Email_header.png?size=1200x0&w=BPhQgTjs4TzCVbCnE8tgJZ7vEAKA] <https://event.montgomerygroup.com/c/14QJF2yYbE9N5emHJ7GY7pqQV> Access a new customer base in 2024 Propak Ghana will return to Accra in 2024 from 23 - 25 April, once again bringing together the packaging, plastics, printing and processing industries in Ghana and surrounding countries. More than 2,500 key buyers and industry representatives will attend to source the missing link in their processing line and acquire new products and solution for their business. Make sure that you won't miss the unmatched opportunity to grow your footprint in the region by having a presence at Propak Ghana 2024 and showcasing your newest innovations to an engaged audience. Be amongst some of the world's leading suppliers who have already confirmed that they'll be exhibiting at Propak next April and more importantly, don't fall behind your competitors! Book your stand now<https://event.montgomerygroup.com/c/14QJJ1UjCnvi3d6TAH5jQo2Ww> Why exhibit? Subject: Comprehensive refrigerated transport services to your business
TextBody: Dear Agristo Team I hope this message finds you well. I am writing to introduce Paula Fish, a leading player in the refrigerated transport industry. With over 150 refrigerated vehicles in our fleet and a robust network of trusted subcontractors, we are well-equipped to meet your transportation needs and reliably. About Us Please find attached a brief presentation of our company, highlighting our extensive experience, commitment to quality, and dedication to meeting unique demands of our client. You will also find out that Paula Fish is much more than a transport company. I hope you find it interesting. Our Services At Paula Fish, we offer a wide range of refrigerated transport services, including: 1. Temperature-Controlled Transport: our state-of-the-art refrigeration units ensure that your goods remain at the desired temperature throughout the journey, preserving their quality and integrity. 2. Nationwide Coverage: with our extensive network, we can provide transportation solutions across the Europe, ensuring timely deliveries to your clients. 3. Real-time Tracking: our team of experienced professionals is dedicated to ensuring the safe and secure transport of your products, adhering to all industry standards and regulations. Why Choose Paula Fish? * Reliability: we take pride in our track record of on-time deliveries and safe handling of cargo. * Customs Solutions: we understand that every client has unique needs, and we tailor our services to meet your specific requirements. * Competitive Pricing: we offer competitive rates without compromising on the quality of service. * Environmental Responsibility: our modern fleet is equipped with eco-friendly technologies, reducing our carbon footprint. We would be delighted to discuss how Paula Fish can assist you to in achieving your transportation goals. Please feel free to contact us if you have any questions. Thank you for considering us as your transportation partner. We look forward to the opportunity to work with you and demonstrate the value we can bring to your business. ► Specyfikacje przelewów za usługi transportowe proszę przesyłać na bts@paulafish.pl<mailto:bts@paulafish.pl> ► When making payments for the use of our transport services, please submit a remittance advice inclusive of invoice numbers covered to bts@paulafish.pl<mailto:bts@paulafish.pl> ► Bitte lassen Się uns für jede Überweisung eine entsprechendes Zahlungsavisierung an bts@paulafish.pl<mailto:bts@paulafish.pl> zukommen. ► En réalisant le paiement, merci d` envoyer les details du virement à l'adresse suivante: bts@paulafish.pl<mailto:bts@paulafish.pl> Pozdrawiam serdecznie /

Subject: Toelevering van draai-,frees- en laswerken vanuit AATEQ - Roemenië
TextBody: T.a.v. aankoopafdeling Geachte We zijn toeleverancier van draai-,frees- en laswerken vanuit Brasov - Roemenië . Ook alle containers op maat gemaakt. We hebben 34 CNC machines en meetgereeschap met Belgisch kapitaal en management. Met 220 mensen runnen wij de productie in 3 ploegen naar de ons gebruikelijke kwaliteitseisen. Wij specialiseren ons op kleinere en middelgrote series en arbeidsintensief werk. Staal, RVS, aluminium, brons en kunstoffen. Ook laswerken, hand&polier-werk, montagejobs. Standaard levertermijn van 4 weken. Wekelijks transport naar Belgie, Nederland en Duitsland Wij staan klaar voor uw oproep, proefbestelling of prijsvraag. Overzicht en afmetingen in bijlage. Zie ook onze website www.aateq.com<http://www.aateq.com> Met vriendelijke groeten --

It is intended only for the addressee(s) stated above. If you have received this e-mail in error, or wish to be removed from the mailing list, please immediately notify US by e-mail and delete the e-mail from your system. TextBody: Hello Lionel, A colleague of mine gave your contact details to me, after he met you on an event. You are interested in one of our frozen potato solutions? Do you have your own distribution channel or partners? And warehouses? Could you provide me some more information concerning your company? Do you have a website? What is your market strategy? TextBody: Good afternoon Lucas, thanks but we already in touch with them but we did not find an agreement in pricelist. Regards Federico Tartarughi Da: Agristo Sales <sales@agristo.com> Inviato: lunedì 2 ottobre 2023 13:59 A: Federico Tartarughi <federicotartarughi@gelfreeze.it> Oggetto: RE: I: french fries information [ thread::T1HCP4pOEUa5hp36X46imHQ:: ] Dear Federico Can you please contact this company. It seems like an interesting proposal. The estimated volume is 1500 ton/year. They are a distributor and are looking for French fries. They are active in the food service. Thank you for taking care! Best regard Lucas Mestdag --------------- Original Message --------------- From: info virocarni [info@virocarni.it] Sent: 2/10/2023 10:24 To: sales@agristo.com<mailto:sales@agristo.com> Subject: I: french fries information [ thread::T1HCP4pOEUa5hp36X46imHQ:: ] Good morning Lucas, how are you? Hope you are very well.. Do you have any news regarding my request for French fries? Please let me know as soon as possible. Many thanks in advance. Romina Da: info virocarni <info@virocarni.it<mailto:info@virocarni.it>> Inviato: giovedì 28 settembre 2023 16:24 A: 'Agristo Sales' <sales@agristo.com<mailto:sales@agristo.com>> Oggetto: R: french fries information [ thread::T1HCP4pOEUa5hp36X46imHQ:: ] Good afternoon Lucas, thank you for your reply. We currently do not sell frozen vegetable products, our core business is the production and processing of especially frozen meats. our customers are wholesalers who serve catering and large-scale retail trade on the national market. we are organized with a network of agents who take care of our sales. we also have 7000 m3 storage warehouses at -20° at our company. we are also present on the Middle Eastern markets for the export of frozen meats produced by us. Since we have requests from our customers for french fries, we would like to start this new collaboration. some of our customers are currently purchasing potatoes in whole trucks, others with groupage, therefore we could manage both solutions, given that we have large storage spaces. as anticipated in the previous email, we have estimated a hypothetical consumption of 1500 MT per year, given that it will clearly depend a lot on the quality/price of the product. Attached our company details. Best regard Romina Da: Agristo Sales <sales@agristo.com<mailto:sales@agristo.com>> Inviato: giovedì 28 settembre 2023 15:54 A: info@virocarni.it<mailto:info@virocarni.it> Oggetto: RE: french fries information [ thread::T1HCP4pOEUa5hp36X46imHQ:: ] Dear, Thank you for your email and your interest in our company. We looking forward to a collaboration! To evaluate your request, we want to get a better picture of your company. Could you inform us and give some detailed information regarding: 1. Do you already purchase frozen (potato) products? What is your experience in this field? 2. If yes, with what brands or companies do you already work? Why do you wish to change? 3. What volumes of fries per SKU do you do annually? 4. Do you have your own distribution channel or partners? And warehouses? 5. Could you provide me some more information concerning your company? Do you have a website? 6. What is your market strategy? Who are your customers? If you have any further questions, please do not hesitate to contact us. With

Subject: ANUGA 2023 - DRIED FRUIT, NUTS and HoReCa products from UAE
TextBody: Dear Sir/Madam, Do you have a plan to attend at ANUGA 2023? We are delighted to invite you to visit our wide range of premium quality of Dried Fruit , Nuts and HoReCa products as follows at the upcoming ANUGA 2023: - FROZEN FRENCH FRIES - TOMATO PASTE - MARGARINE & BUTTER - SKIMMED MILK POWDER - CAVIAR - PRAWNS - FREEZE-DRIED FRUIT & VEGETABLES - CUMIN SEED - LIQUORICE extract/powder - DRIED APRICOT - ROSE BUD AND ROSE PETALS - SAFFRON - RICE - PISTACHIOS and PISTACHIO KERNEL - SULTANAS/RAISINS - DATES and DATES' products (Paste/Diced/Sliced/Syrup/Concentrate) ORGANIC/CONVENTIONAL - FIGS and FIG paste - BARBERRIES - SAFFRON Glad to invite you to have a quick look on our e-catalog https://fortunefood.ae/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/fortunefood.pdf Our knowledgeable team will be available to answer any questions you may have and provide you with detailed information about all our products. You are cordially invited to join us for an enjoyable meeting of sampling and networking with other food enthusiasts. Thank you for considering our invitation, and hope to see you soon at ANUGA 2023 Hall 2.1 | Stand: E049. Cologne, Germany, 7-11 OCT 2023. Looking forward to hearing from you soon. Khasim Mehdi Managing Director FORTUNE FOODS N SPICES TRADING FZCO Dubai - United Arab Emirates ***** [cid:image001.jpg@01D9F49A.5E3DA720]

Subject: Transport cooperation
TextBody: Hello, I would like to offer you our services in the field of refrigerated transport. I know the reading too long messages is boring, so here's a short story about us. We are a company with 30 years of experience in transport. We operate in Germany, Belgium, the Netherlands, Great Britain and northern Poland. We are in your neighborhood every day. We would be most interested in shipments to Germany and northern Poland. Here are the details of our offerings: * We have 23 VOLVO trucks and 1 SCANIA truck authorized for international road transportation of goods. All our trucks are equipped with GPS and phones. * Our reefer semi-trailers, from SCHMITZ and LAMBERET, can accommodate up to 33 euro-pallets. Each trailer is equipped with a minimum of 2 secure bars and a temperature electronic monitor and printer. * We hold an IFS Certificate at the Higher level, with an impressive evaluation score of 95.80% Should you have any questions, please feel free to contact me at any time. 😊 --

Subject: export friet
TextBody: Beste , Dank u wel voor uw e-mail en uw interesse in Agristo! Om uw verzoek te beoordelen, willen we graag een beter beeld krijgen van uw bedrijf. Kunt u ons informeren en gedetailleerde informatie verstrekken over: Koopt u al bevroren (aardappel)producten? Wat is uw ervaring op dit gebied? Zo ja, met welke merken of bedrijven werkt u al samen? Waarom wilt u veranderen? Welke volumes frites per SKU verwerkt u jaarlijks? Heeft u uw eigen distributiekanaal of partners? En magazijnen? Kunt u wat meer informatie verstrekken over uw bedrijf? Heeft u een website? Wat is uw marktstrategie? Wie zijn uw klanten? Hoe bent u op de hoogte gekomen van Agristo? Welke specifieke producten zoekt u bij ons te kopen? Als u nog verdere vragen heeft, aarzel dan niet om contact met ons op te nemen. Met vriendelijke groet, --------------- Original Message ---------------

Subject: lening
TextBody: Hallo meneer/mevrouw, Wij zijn niet van plan uw tijd te verspillen. Wij verstrekken leningen aan particulieren en bedrijven. Het rentepercentage zal 2% per jaar bedragen. Wij hebben de capaciteit om projecten op deze gebieden te financieren; vastgoedontwikkeling, bouw, mijnbouw, olie en gas, luchtvaartmaatschappijen en diverse handelsactiviteiten. Bij interesse graag het volgende doorgeven: 1- Volledige naam: 2- Vereist leningbedrag: 3- Terugverdientijd (1 – 30 jaar): 4- Telefoonnummer: 5- Whatsapp-nummer: Zodra ik bovenstaande informatie ontvang, stuur ik u de leenvoorwaarden toe. Uw terugbetalingsplan gaat in na 6 maanden (6 maanden respijtperiode). De financiering duurt ongeveer 7 bankdagen vanaf de dag dat u uw leningsaanvraag indient. Reageer ons voor meer informatie. Ondergetekende Uwe Wanner

Subject: The Vietnam market is Booming
TextBody: Can't read this email? Please click here to view it in your browser. [https://oesallworld.msgfocus.com/files/amf_overseas_exhib/project_1388/Picture4.png]<https://oesallworld.msgfocus.com/c/11ltYkAuCxlBoZB4B8etUa6Gm> VIETNAM OFFERS A BOOMING MARKET FOR EXPORT The Vietnam market is a thriving marketplace - they have one of the fastest growing economies in South East Asia leading to higher demand for quality food products. Food and Hotel Vietnam (19-21 March 2024) is the flagship show for the country and offers the ideal opportunity to meet buyers and distributors' from the marketplace seeking new food and drink products to import. [https://oesallworld.msgfocus.com/files/amf_overseas_exhib/project_1388/Award.png] Once again, we will be running the highly regarded Vietnam Culinary Challenge<https://oesallworld.msgfocus.com/c/11ltYH4CcMK6oOd5G0b3HlfMv> (Salon Culinary) which gives chef's an opportunity to compete at the highest level with their contemporaries. Ho Chi Minh City has many premium restaurants and the event will attract the best chef's and buyers from the restaurant sector. We also run a barista competition to capitalise on the rapid growth of café culture. In addition to our food service visitors we also attract supermarket buyers and distributors' from across the region who want to bring new products to their domestic markets. KEY TRENDS IN VIETNAM [https://finctr.stripocdn.email/content/guids/CABINET_6bcd234424bf1c4e04f2cbc81410e186acf2bc4f1e665495cf7ffb7cf584eb62/images/6.png] Growing Disposable Income With an emerging middle class, a higher disposable income leads to greater interest in food from health and wellbeing products through to sweets & snacks, dairy, baby food, premium gifting and of course quality meat. [https://finctr.stripocdn.email/content/guids/CABINET_6bcd234424bf1c4e04f2cbc81410e186acf2bc4f1e665495cf7ffb7cf584eb62/images/7.png] Changing Lifestyles Vietnam has a young population with 70% of the population under 35. They are embracing different food styles and lifestyle with a greater emphasis on convenience and quality food products, in contrast there is also greater interest in health and wellbeing products. [https://finctr.stripocdn.email/content/guids/CABINET_6bcd234424bf1c4e04f2cbc81410e186acf2bc4f1e665495cf7ffb7cf584eb62/images/8.png] Urbanisation Impact The growth of urbanisation has led to a café culture - giving many opportunities for snacking and premium beverages. All these key trends mean that Vietnam offers a vibrant market - there's never been a better time to come on board and activate your presence within the marketplace. Subject: New Business Inquiry - Australia FCL
TextBody: Hi! No problems. Pleasure. This is a difficult question to answer. I believe the first shipment we would seek a order Qty around 10Tonne. After the product has been introduced to selective clients, and we have received postive feedback we would order in lots of 40Ft FCLs. It is at this point in time we would release the website, and implement marketing plans. From this point in time, given the dire situation with French Fries in Australia/ NZ, and if the product is of same or better quality of Mydibels product (these guys are perhaps our biggest competitor) it would be mind boggling the volumes we could attain. You must understand, our selective network is made up of some of Australia's most well respected chefs, among them a few celebrity Chefs, of which utilising our network plays a role in our marketing strategy. I wouldn't want to lead you down a broken trail of disappointment, but the volumes after we move past the initial 2 -3 months could grow to well over 1000+ tonnes / Annually of a single SKU. In saying this, the quality and price point is key. Given our ambition to sell direct to venues, it will be much easier to meet price expectations, however the quality must be there. Hope this gives you some idea of where this could head. Appreciate your time, On Thu, 5 Oct 2023, 23:18 Agristo Sales, <sales@agristo.com<mailto:sales@agristo.com>> wrote: Dear Mr Fenton Thank you for answering the list of questions. Now we have a better image of who you are and what you do. May I ask you how much volume you think you will order every month? If there are any questions feel free to ask, I will help you anytime.

Subject: Onze diensten
TextBody: Geachte, Bent u op zoek naar een gespecialiseerde productiearbeider voor uw bedrijf? Belfood Services, is een klantgericht onder aannemingsbedrijf dat een brede waaier van diensten. Aanbiedt en hierdoor optimaal kan inspelen op de evoluerende behoeften van haar klanten. Om aan al hun specifieke eisen te voldoen krijgen onze mensen aangepaste interne opleiding. Dit maakt het ons mogelijk om een kwalitatieve service op maat van de klant samen te stellen. Wij doen hoofdzakelijk: · Productie en Band arbeiders van alle soorten voedingswaren · Verpakking van alle soorten voedingswaren · Verpakking van alle soorten suiker-chocoladewaren · Verpakking van alle soorten vleeswaren · Algemene polyvalente arbeiders Onze mensen staan klaar om uw producten te verwerken en in te pakken. Wenst U meer informatie over ons bedrijf, aarzel dan niet om ons te contacteren. Met vriendelijke groeten Alperen Ugurlu General Managing Belfood Horeca Service Bv Prinsenlaan 1D 9140 Temse

Subject: Let's Talk Coconuts at Anuga Trade Fair 2023!
TextBody: Hi Exhibitors, I'm Viji, a fourth-gen coconut farmer, representing Vashini Exports. Well recognised for shipping out top-notch coconut products across 25 countries worldwide, since almost a decade, this time we wish to make it even bigger with our exclusive range of coconut products. We are headed to the Anuga Trade Fair from October 7th to 10th, 2023. We wish to upscale our coconut game! We wish you to join us in our league of featuring supreme quality goodies, like- Mature Coconuts - Size: 30/35/40/50/60 Coconut Sugar Coconut Chips Desiccated Coconut Virgin Coconut Oil Coconut Bowls (made of natural coconut shells) Coconut Milk Tender Coconut An entire bunch of frozen fruits and vegetable varieties I'd love to catch up if you're up for it during the event to discuss potential business collaborations. Thanks for considering a meet-up. Can't wait to see what Anuga has in store! Warm

Subject: Good day
TextBody: My dearest one, My Name is Lilian Williams, 22 years old girl. I wish to inquire about your services to be my foreign partner / investor and support me to transfer and manage my inherited funds by investing in profit making ventures like buying of company shares or Real Estate Trust Fund in your country. I have a reasonable sum that I inherited from my father Mr. Fedy Williams, which I would like you to help me invest in your country. Below is the major reason I am contacting you. (1) To provide a new empty bank account in which this money would be transferred. if you don't want us to use your personal account. (2) To serve as a guardian of this fund since the bank insisted that their agreement with my father was that I provide a foreign partner before releasing the fund. (3) To make arrangements for me to come over to your country to further my education and to secure a resident permit in your country. Please reply to me as soon as you read this message and documents so that I will know how to proceed. Thanks yours kindest, Lilian

Subject: urgent
TextBody: Dear Sir, There is an ongoing Tender in the West Africa projects development commission for the supply of potatoes,. mushroom and different products to the commission.The commission is hereby inviting foreign companies whose products meet international standards to participate in this tender. Tender documents defining listed items, terms of payment etc will be released to interested /eligible companies upon indication of interest. Only companies who are cognizant with the tendering/bidding formalities and are willing to abide by the guidelines can apply. Tendering will be conducted through the National Competitive Tendering procedures as specified in the Public Procurement Act, 2006 (Act 663) and the Guidelines of the Public Procurement commission (PPC). So I would like to know if you can handle the supply order of your company's products to the project coordinator . . I am a commission agent. Thanks, PETER ANSAH PICAN LTD 24 LIBERTY ROAD, ACCRA-

Subject: Import to Mongolia
TextBody: Good morning, I’m looking for a french fries distributor for a Mongolian food supplier and importer company. We are interested in getting a price range if possible. Could you tell us what would a 40 ton container of the following costs please: -Fries fries -Sweet potato fries -Waffle cut fries -Roast potatoes Your reply and cooperation is much appreciated. Looking forward to hearing from you. Warm

Subject: Goededag
TextBody: Liefste, Mijn naam is Nora Alex. Ik zou graag willen weten wat uw diensten zijn om mijn partner/buitenlandse investeerder te zijn en mij te ondersteunen bij het overdragen en beheren van mijn geld in een winstgevend bedrijf en hoe ik aandelen of onroerend goed door het bedrijf kan kopen. Ik heb een redelijk bedrag dat ik van mijn vader heb geërfd dat ik wil dat u mij helpt te investeren in uw land. Let op: hieronder vindt u de belangrijkste reden waarom ik contact met u opneemt. (1) Om een nieuwe lege bankrekening aan te bieden waarop dit geld zou worden overgemaakt. Als u niet wilt dat wij uw persoonlijke account gebruiken. (2) Om als bewaker van dit fonds te dienen, aangezien de bank erop stond dat hun afspraak met mijn vader was dat ik een buitenlandse partner ter beschikking zou stellen voordat het fonds zou worden vrijgegeven. (3) Om regelingen te treffen dat ik naar uw land kom om mijn opleiding voort te zetten en om een verblijfsvergunning in uw land te verkrijgen. Beantwoord mij alstublieft zodra u dit bericht leest, zodat ik weet hoe ik verder moet gaan. Hartelijk dank, Mevrouw Nora Alex.

Subject: La vie Import  & Export
TextBody: Dear Mr Wally It is indeed the 10/10, not coated. We can pack that for you if you work with private label (see the requirements below). I have to tell you that we have exclusive partnerships in the United States. If you want to work with us I will have to discuss this internally. Our requirements in order to set up a private label: MOQ of 500 ton per SKU per year We ask a financial guarantee of € 2000 per SKU to start up. After the MOQ is exceeded we transfer this amount back. Agristo will arrange everything to produce the foil with our partners. Designs come from the customer If the design is ready, it takes up to 2 months for the foil to be ready to go into production Afterwards if expected volumes are clear we could make sure to have a minimum volume on stock so it would take 1 week then from order to delivery. If you have any other questions, let me know! Have a good day.
